{"name": "myfletify", "metadata": {"name": "myfletify", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/tct123/MyFletifyHTML", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["flet", "bs4"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1733475940}, "documentation": ["# MyFletifyHTML\n\nMyFletifyHTML is a Python package for converting HTML content into Flet code. It allows you to embed HTML code in your Flet app\n\n## Installation\n### (Not avalaible for now,...) \n```bash\npip install fletify\n```\n### Alternative\nInstall via Github and use the `example.py` to test Fletify\n\n```bash\npip install git+https://github.com/tct123/MyFletifyHTML.git\n```\n## Usage\n```python\nimport flet as ft\nfrom myfletify import FletifyHTML\n\n# Example HTML content\nhtml_content = \"<p>This is a <b>paragraph</b> with <a href='#'>a link</a></p>\"\n\n# Create a FletifyHTML instance\nfletify = FletifyHTML(html_content)\n\n# Get the Flet code\nflet_code = fletify.get_flet()\n\ndef main(page: ft.Page):\n\n    #Display the output, by adding it on the page \n    page.add(flet_code)\n    page.update()\n\nft.app(target=main)\n```\n# OutPut:\n![test1](test1.PNG)\n\n`FletifyHTML()` can receive the HTML file containing the content to be displayed, `FletifyHTML(html=<path-to-your-html-file>)` \n\n## Features\n\nFor now, **Fletify** support the following HTML tags:\n\n`img`, `ul`, `ol`, `li`, `a`, `b`, `strong`, `i`, `em`, `u`, `mark`, `span`, `div`, `p`, `code`, `h1`, `h2`, `h3`, `h4`, `h5`, `h6`, `table`, `tr`, `th`, `td`\nFletify doesn't support CSS style however, it supports inline style using the `style` attribute.\n#### eg:\n```html\n<img style=\"width: 200; height: 200; background-color:yellow; border-radius: 5; border: 3 solid #336699; margin:40\" src=\"https://picsum.photos/200/200?10\" alt=\"Example Image\">\n```\nthese are the supported style properties\n`color`, `background-color`, `font-family`, `font-size`, `text-align`, `text-decoration`, `display`, `justify-content`, `margin`, `padding`, `border-radius`, `border`, `width`, `height`\n\n## Contributing\nIf you'd like to contribute to FletifyHTML, please open an issue or submit a pull request.\n\n\ud83d\udea8 Give FletifyHTML a try and tell us what you think about it.\n\n## License\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License - see the [LICENSE](LICENSE) file for details.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "myfletify.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "myfletify.utils.RenderHTML", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "myfletify.utils.RenderHTML.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "file", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "encoding", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "myfletify.utils.RenderHTML.__repr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "myfletify.utils.RenderHTML.display", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "myfletify.utils.RenderHTML.__str__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "myfletify", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "myfletify.MyFletifyHTML", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "myfletify.MyFletifyHTML.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "html", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "myfletify.MyFletifyHTML.get_flet", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": [{"name": "myfletify.convert_html_to_flet", "xref": {"fqname": "myfletify.converter.convert_html_to_flet", "project": null}}, {"name": "myfletify.RenderHTML", "xref": {"fqname": "myfletify.utils.RenderHTML", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "myfletify.converter", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "myfletify.converter.convert_html_to_flet", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "html_file", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "myfletify.parser", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "myfletify.parser.parse_html_to_flet", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "element", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "myfletify.parser.html_table_to_flet", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "element", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "container", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "myfletify.parser.parse_inline_styles", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "style_string", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "myfletify.parser.get_style", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "element", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "is_a_mapping", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "myfletify.parser.html_to_flet_style_mapping", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "myfletify.parser.HTML", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "myfletify.parser.HTML.TEXT_STYLE_DECORATION", "type": null, "document